# NOTE: .env is intentionally NOT ignored. The builder stage needs it so
# `next build` can inline NEXT_PUBLIC_* into the client bundle (no enumerated
# build args to forget). The final runtime image is assembled from the
# standalone output only and never COPYs .env, so secrets are not shipped in
# the published image. If you build on a machine without .env, provide the
# NEXT_PUBLIC_* values some other way before building.
